  <div class="general-contact-content">

<strong>What’s the cover?</strong>
All shows are NOTAFLOF (No one turned away for lack of funds), so all you need is your membership card. We encourage donating towards the night’s bands—the recommended donation varies from show to show. 
We can take payment via cash, card, or apple pay. 
<br>
<strong>Why do you check IDs?</strong>
Some door volunteers prefer to check IDs and X the hands of people under 21. Even though we are a sober space, many find it helpful to know when they are interacting with an older or younger person. 
<br>
<strong>Why do I have to pay membership?</strong>
We are a collective-based venue, which means that your $5/year fee makes you a part of the Seventh Circle collective. This gives us funds to keep the space open while giving YOU a say in the direction of Seventh Circle! It also helps ensure that we can keep all our shows donation-only. 
<br>
<strong>Is there re-entry?</strong>
After you first check in with the door person and get your wristband or your hand marked, you’re welcome to come and go as you please! No need to check in with us upon re-entry. 
<br>
<strong>Do you sell food? </strong>
We don’t regularly sell food or drinks, but there are several restaurants, food trucks, and gas stations in walking or nearby driving distance.
<br>
<strong>Is smoking allowed?</strong>
You can smoke while in the courtyard or outside the venue. Please do not smoke in the house, in the show space, or in the green room/practice space. 


